text.tspan: People living in long-standing electoral democracies, World
Political regimes based on the classification and assessment by Skaaning et al. (2015). Electoral
democracies are understood here as political systems in which citizens have the right to choose the chief
executive and the legislature in multi-party, uncertain elections.
Data source: Skaaning et al. (2015); Gapminder (v6); HYDE (v3.2); UN (2022)
